  "text": "The wire kernel analysis used in [CITATION_1] may be used for curved wire segments. This is done by modifying the expression for in [CITATION_2] to (28) Note that the tangent vector in (28) is a function of position along the source wire segment, since it is not constant for a curved wire segment.",
